cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about improving the speed and energy consumption of CNN-based image classification and object detection tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a model-level approach, which involves optimizing the architecture of the CNN models, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also discusses the trade-offs between system speed/energy consumption and accuracy, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves experiments on different CNN models and datasets, which could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
